    "ts": "2026-03-16T18:13:24+00:00",
    "headline": "LME Trading Restored After Two-Hour Halt Roiled Metals Markets",
    "summary": "The failure came at a critical moment in the metals calendar, as the market approaches the third Wednesday of the month — the main focus of liquidity in the LME’s contracts — just as commodity prices are being rocked by the war in Iran.  The disruption came as the LME encountered an issue with its primary electronic matching engine, a spokesperson for the exchange said after trading resumed.  The metals markets have been hit by several outages over recent months, with the LME facing a one-hour delay to the start of trading on Jan. 30, while rival exchange operator CME Group faced a 10-hour suspension that roiled global markets in November.",
